last_episode_to_air.name: Midsummer Magic
last_episode_to_air.overview: As preparations begin for the Midsummer party, the sun goes missing from Moominvalley.

name: Moominvalley
overview: Follow the life and adventures of curious, kind and idealistic Moomintroll. A typical hero in a coming-of-age story, Moomintroll tries to tackle the puzzle of growing up to his true, individualistic self while remaining a beloved part of the family.

episodes.name: Little My Moves In
episodes.overview: When Mymble arrives unannounced at Moominhouse with all of her unruly children, the Moomin family's renowned tolerance is tested to breaking point.

episodes.name: The Spring Tune
episodes.overview: Snufkin's return journey to Moominvalley is disrupted by an overly friendly forest creature. Is it time to hurry back and see his friend Moomintroll?

episodes.name: The Last Dragon in the World
episodes.overview: Moomintroll finds a real dragon, just the right size to be a pet. All he wants is for the little dragon to love him back, but can it be tamed?

episodes.name: Moominsummer Madness
episodes.overview: When a great flood fills the valley, the Moomins find somewhere new to live - a floating theatre! But is somebody already living there?

episodes.name: The Golden Tale
episodes.overview: Moominpappa is inspired to put on a play all about his adventurous youth. But the pressure to fill his father's shoes makes Moomintroll's tail hairs fall out!

episodes.name: The Secret of the Hattifatteners
episodes.overview: Snork Maiden encourages Moomintroll to take her on a voyage to an island where Moominpappa once encountered the storm-chasing Hattifatteners.

episodes.name: Snufkin and the Park Keeper
episodes.overview: Incensed by the Park Keeper, Snufkin plots a cunning revenge. But when his friends get the blame for his actions, Snufkin must come to their rescue.

episodes.name: Monster Fish
episodes.overview: When Moominpappa and Moomintroll's 'story battle' gets out of hand, a monstrous fish comes to life and Moominhouse is overrun by a wild jungle.

episodes.name: Night of the Groke
episodes.overview: Moomintroll's mind starts to play tricks on him when he's left home alone overnight for the first time. But soon, his worst fears are realised.

episodes.name: Moominmamma's Maid
episodes.overview: When Mrs Fillyjonk embarrasses the Moomins into getting a maid, the Moominhouse becomes much better organised, but at what cost?

episodes.name: Ghost Story
episodes.overview: Moomintroll uses the services of a little ghost to convince Snork Maiden that he is brave. But when his trick backfires, Moomintroll is the one who needs saving.

episodes.name: The Invisible Child
episodes.overview: The Moomin family's attempts to help a shy girl only make things worse. Can Moomintroll learn to listen long enough to understand what she really needs?

episodes.name: Midwinter Ancestor
episodes.overview: Moomintroll faces his toughest challenge yet when he wakes up too early from hibernation. To survive the perils of winter, he must find his primal side.

episodes.name: Moomin's Winter Follies
episodes.overview: When a charismatic winter sports champion arrives in the valley, Moomintroll struggles to win back Snorkmaiden's affections.

episodes.name: The Fire Spirit
episodes.overview: As the valley evacuates under the threat of volcanic eruption, Moomintroll helps Snufkin on a perilous quest to return a lost fire spirit to her home.

episodes.name: Moominpappa & Son
episodes.overview: In an attempt to set a good example for his family, Moominpappa becomes a changed Moomin when he decides to get a job. But all is not what it seems.

episodes.name: Little My Moves Out
episodes.overview: When Moomintroll gets his wish to be free of the troublesome Little My, he soon comes to regret it

episodes.name: The Strange Case of Mrs Fillyjonk
episodes.overview: When Moominmamma is accused of an unlikely crime, Moomintroll turns detective to try to save her. Can he succeed where his father couldn't?

episodes.name: The Hobgoblin's Hat
episodes.overview: Moomintroll and his friends find a magical and mysterious hat. While fun to begin with, they soon realise that the hat is dangerous.

episodes.name: Thingumy and Bob
episodes.overview: In his desire for more independence, Moomintroll pushes Moominmamma away. But he soon becomes jealous when she finds a new outlet for her motherly love.

episodes.name: The Trial
episodes.overview: A trial is set to find the rightful owner of a mysterious ruby. But in fighting over the precious gem, what truths will the inhabitants of Moominvalley learn?

episodes.name: Farewell Snorkmaiden
episodes.overview: Moomintroll decides to move into his own place with Snorkmaiden. But is he ready to give up the care and comfort of Moominmamma and Moominpappa?

episodes.name: Moominpappa's Island
episodes.overview: Moominpappa is desperate to guide his family and prove that they can thrive on a desolate island but it only seems to push them further apart.

episodes.name: Moominmamma's Mural
episodes.overview: Moominmamma is so homesick that she finds a magical way to travel back to Moominvalley until she becomes trapped.

episodes.name: Moomintroll and the Seahorses
episodes.overview: Being stuck on the island with his parents, Moomintroll realises he needs his own space, so he starts his own secret adventure.

episodes.name: November
episodes.overview: Puzzled by the continued absence of the Moomin family, the inhabitants of Moominvalley try their best to welcome new guest, Toffle.

episodes.name: Homecoming
episodes.overview: The Moomins return home to find a 'wise leader' telling everyone there should be no rules, and Moominvalley falls into chaos.

episodes.name: Moomintroll's Grand Adventure
episodes.overview: When Moomintroll's sea adventure ends poorly, he meets Snork and tries to impress his new friend with tall tales. Will his fibs catch up with him?

episodes.name: Brisk & Breezy
episodes.overview: When Mr Brisk sets up a summer camp, Little My joins the camp and puts Brisk through a series of rigorous tests.

episodes.name: Inventing Snork
episodes.overview: Moomintroll tries to help Snork make friends in the valley using his clever inventions, but Snork's gifts backfire.

episodes.name: The Stinky Caper
episodes.overview: When Moomintroll accidentally becomes an accomplice to a burglary, the Moomins try to put things right by staging a reverse heist, but nothing goes to plan.

episodes.name: Toffle's Tall Tales
episodes.overview: Moomintroll and Sniff volunteer to walk Toffle home through the woods, but all is not what it seems.

episodes.name: Winter Secrets
episodes.overview: When Stinky breaks out of jail, the Moomins postpone their winter hibernation to shelter their neighbours and hunt for the fugitive.

episodes.name: Lonely Mountain
episodes.overview: Moomintroll cancels his hibernation to go find Snufkin in the mysterious Lonely Mountains, but Snufkin doesn't like having his solitude disrupted.

episodes.name: Mrs Fillyjonk's Last Hurrah
episodes.overview: When Mrs Fillyjonk thinks she is not long for this world, Moominpappa steps in to make all her wildest dreams come true.

episodes.name: Snufkin and the Fairground
episodes.overview: After Snufkin advises a silence-loving Hemulen to leave his noisy job at the fairground, he is left to run the rides with the help of his friends.

episodes.name: Call of the Hattifatteners
episodes.overview: When a lost Hattifattener's spark starts to fade, Moominpappa, the Fisherman and Little My set out to sea to return it home.

episodes.name: Moominmamma's Flying Dream
episodes.overview: Moomintroll learns of Moominmamma's love of hot air ballooning and decides to make her dream come true.

episodes.name: Midsummer Magic
episodes.overview: As preparations begin for the Midsummer party, the sun goes missing from Moominvalley.
